OL,3,C'Hope you get cancer': The abuse aimed
OL,4,Cat rail company social team
OL,6,FIn the last four years Northern has
OL,7,Frecorded 745 public order offences
OL,8,Fagainst its staff on trains or in
OL,9,Frailway stations. Seventy-three of
OL,10,Fthose resulted in convictions.
OL,12,FSome workers who have face-to-face
OL,13,Fcontact with passengers use body-worn
OL,14,Fcameras to record abusive behaviour.
OL,16,FIn one such incident a conductor was
OL,17,Fphysically assaulted by a man who had
OL,18,Fbeen refused entry to a train from
OL,19,FLeeds to Manchester after he became
OL,20,Fabusive.
